53. att
54. handla
55. om
56. invandrare

There are 56 words in the text.

The average number of words per sentence (AvF) is calculated by dividing the total number of words by the total number of sentences. Since the text has 3 sentences and 1 set of hyphenated words set off at the start of a sentence, we divide 56 words by 5 units that resemble a sentence which gives us about 11.2 words per sentence.

The average number of letters per word (AvL) is calculated by counting the total number of letters in the text and dividing by the total number of words. The text has 299 letters in total. 299 letters divided by 56 words gives us an average of 5.3 letters per word.

The average number of short words (AvS) is calculated by counting the number of short words and dividing by the total number of words, then multiplying by 100. In this case there are 7 words with three letters or less which is 7 short words * (100 / 56) = 12.5%

We plug these values into the LIX readability score formula to get:
LIX = (11.2 + 5.3 * 0.125) / 2
LIX = (11.2 + 0.6625) / 2
LIX = (11.8625) / 2
LIX = 5.93125

So,
LIX = 59.